tsebhi

The main flavor notes are from that berbere — it's earthy, it's spicy, it's quintessentially horn african. 

And the tomato and the butter are serving to both boost and balance those flavors. 

It's robust, but it's nuanced at the same time.

So given the limited number of ingredients, you should most definitely give this one a go, 

but of course, if you've got an Eritrean restaurant nearby please give them your business — 

especially during this terrible time for the food industry.